zadanie 1

Przygotowanie danych

Wczytanie danych:

australia <- read.csv("australia.csv")


PodziaÅ‚ danych:

m <- dim(australia)[1]             # m to ilosc rekordow


ktore_treningowy <- sample(m, floor(0.6 * m)) # 60% danych idze do zbioru uczacego
ktore_walidacyjny <- sample(setdiff(1:m, ktore_treningowy), floor(0.2 * m)) # 20% do walidacyjnego
ktore_testowy <- 1:m %>% setdiff(ktore_treningowy) %>% setdiff(ktore_walidacyjny) # ostatnie 20% do testowego

australia_set <- australia %>% select(-RainTomorrow)
train <- australia_set[ktore_treningowy,]
valid <- australia_set[ktore_walidacyjny,]
test <- australia_set[ktore_testowy,]
train_label <- australia[ktore_treningowy,"RainTomorrow"]
valid_label <- australia[ktore_walidacyjny,"RainTomorrow"]
test_label <- australia[ktore_testowy,"RainTomorrow"]


Sprawdzenie, czy losowanie nie podzieliÅ‚o zmiennej celu w sposob niepozadany:

train_label %>% mean
## [1] 0.2217594
valid_label %>% mean
## [1] 0.2132223
test_label %>% mean
## [1] 0.2227933


Standaryzacja zmiennych:

srednie <- sapply(train, mean)
odchylenia <- sapply(train, var) %>% sqrt

wycentruj <- function(num){
  (num - srednie)/odchylenia
}

# wycentrowanie zbiorow
for(i in 1:dim(train)[1]){
  train[i,] <- wycentruj(train[i,])
}
for(i in 1:dim(valid)[1]){
  valid[i,] <- wycentruj(test[i,])
}
for(i in 1:dim(test)[1]){
  test[i,] <- wycentruj(test[i,])
}


Sprawdzenie poprawnoÅ›ci standaryzacji:

plot(sort(valid$MinTemp))


WyglÄ…da bardzo podobnie do rozkÅ‚adu normalnego ;)
Ostatnie przygotowania przed modelowaniem:

# powrot zmiennej celu do danych
train$RainTomorrow <- train_label
test$RainTomorrow <- test_label
valid$RainTomorrow <- valid_label


# podzial w kroswalidacji
M <- 10

# definicja taska
label_task <- makeClassifTask(data = train, target = "RainTomorrow")
# definicja CrossValidacji
cv <- makeResampleDesc("CV", iters = M)

Las Losowy

Hiperparametry:
1. num.trees - IloÅ›Ä‡ drzew w lesie
2. mtry - maksymalna iloÅ›Ä‡ zmiennych, na ktÃ³rych podejmowany jest podziaÅ‚ w drzewach

# las losowy
quiet( classif_lrn <- makeLearner("classif.ranger", par.vals = list(num.trees = 500, mtry = 3), predict.type = "prob") )
quiet( r <- resample(classif_lrn, label_task, cv, models = TRUE) )

WybÃ³r najleprzego z lasÃ³w(z najwiekszym AUC na zbiorze walidacyjnym):

AUC_test <- numeric(M)
AUC_valid <- numeric(M)
AUC_max <- 0
model_forest <- NULL
for(i in 1:M){
  model <- r$models[[i]]
  
  pred_valid <- predict(model, newdata = valid)
  
  quiet( ROC <- roc(predictor = pred_valid$data$prob.1, response = valid_label) )
  if(auc(ROC) %>% as.numeric() > AUC_max){
    AUC_max <- auc(ROC) %>% as.numeric()
    model_forest <- model
  }
}


Teraz model_forest jest wybranym modelem. Przetestujmy go:

pred_test <- predict(model_forest, newdata = test)

# wykres ROC i miara AUC
quiet( ROC <- roc(predictor = pred_test$data$prob.1, response = test_label) )
plot(ROC)

forest_AUC <- as.numeric(auc(ROC))
auc(ROC)
## Area under the curve: 0.8873
# logarytmiczna funkcja straty
forest_LogLoss <- LogLoss(pred_test$data$prob.1, test_label)
LogLoss(pred_test$data$prob.1, test_label)
## [1] 0.3348752
# bÅ‚Ä…d Å›redniokwadratowy
forest_MSE <- MSE(pred_test$data$prob.1, test_label)
MSE(pred_test$data$prob.1, test_label)
## [1] 0.1042086

Drzewo decyzyjne

Hiperparametry:
1. minsplit - najmniejsza iloÅ›Ä‡ obserwacji potrzebna do podzialu. 2. maxdepth - najwieksza gÅ‚Ä™bokoÅ›Ä‡ drzewa

# decision tree
quiet( dt_learner <- makeLearner("classif.rpart", predict.type = "prob", par.vals = list("minsplit" = 10, "maxdepth" = 25)) )

zadanie 2

Wczytanie danych:

data <- read.csv("allegro-api-transactions.csv")

Pozbycie siÄ™ powtÃ³rek:

data$it_location %>% table %>% length # 10_056
## [1] 10056
data$it_location %>% str_to_upper() %>% table %>% length # 7_903
## [1] 7903
data$it_location <- data$it_location %>% str_to_upper()

PodziaÅ‚ na treningowy i testowy:

m <- dim(data)[1]
ktore <- sample(m, floor(0.8 * m)) # 80% danych do treningowego
train <- data[ktore,]
test <- data[-ktore,]

train_original <- train
test_original <- test
Target encoding
# it_location
srednie_it_location <- train %>% group_by(it_location) %>% summarise(avr_price = mean(price))
train <- train %>% left_join(srednie_it_location, by = c("it_location" = "it_location")) %>% select(-it_location, it_location_avr_price = avr_price)
test <- test %>% left_join(srednie_it_location, by = c("it_location" = "it_location")) %>% select(-it_location, it_location_avr_price = avr_price)
# main_category
srednie_main_category <- train %>% group_by(main_category) %>% summarise(avr_price = mean(price))
train <- train %>% left_join(srednie_main_category, by = c("main_category" = "main_category")) %>% select(-main_category, main_category_avr_price = avr_price)
test <- test %>% left_join(srednie_main_category, by = c("main_category" = "main_category")) %>% select(-main_category, main_category_avr_price = avr_price)

train <- train %>% select(pay_option_on_delivery, it_is_allegro_standard, it_quantity,
                         it_is_brand_zone, it_seller_rating, it_location_avr_price,
                         main_category_avr_price, price)
test <- test %>% select(pay_option_on_delivery, it_is_allegro_standard, it_quantity,
                          it_is_brand_zone, it_seller_rating, it_location_avr_price,
                          main_category_avr_price, price)


task <- makeRegrTask(id = "lvr", data = train, target = "price")
lrn <- makeLearner("regr.glm")
model <- train(lrn, task)
wynik <- predict(model, newdata = train)
sredniokwadratowy_target <- MSE(wynik$data$response, wynik$data$truth)
sredniokwadratowy_target %>% sqrt # czyli bardzo duze
## [1] 317.0468
R2_target <- cor(wynik$data$response, wynik$data$truth)^2
R2_target
## [1] 0.1097425
one-hot encodeing


1-of-n:

train <- train_original
test <- test_original

train <- train %>% select(pay_option_on_delivery, it_is_allegro_standard, it_quantity,
                          it_is_brand_zone, it_seller_rating, main_category, price)
test <- test %>% select(pay_option_on_delivery, it_is_allegro_standard, it_quantity,
                        it_is_brand_zone, it_seller_rating, main_category, price)

train <- train %>% createDummyFeatures(target = "price", method = "1-of-n")
test <- test %>% createDummyFeatures(target = "price", method = "1-of-n")

# pozbycie sie polskich liter
colnames(train) <- colnames(train) %>% str_replace_all("Å¼", "z") %>%
  str_replace_all("Ã³", "o") %>% str_replace_all("Ä…", "a") %>% str_replace_all("Å›", "s") %>% 
  str_replace_all("Å‚", "l") %>% str_replace_all("Ä™", "e")

task <- makeRegrTask(id = "dupa2", data = train, target = "price")
lrn <- makeLearner("regr.glm")
model <- train(lrn, task)
wynik <- predict(model, newdata = train)
sredniokwadratowy <- MSE(wynik$data$response, wynik$data$truth)
sredniokwadratowy %>% sqrt # czyli bardzo duze, wieksze
